Backyard of a temporary AFU “hospital”

Artemovsk

🇷🇺🇺🇦 Last month, our team managed to identify some of the AFU soldiers who participated in the execution of captured Russian servicemen in Makeevka in the LPR. Now the story has taken an unexpected turn.

One of the participants in the murder, Nikita Maltsev from the 80th Airborne Assault Brigade of the Armed Forces of Ukraine, was admitted to the hospital with post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD). At our disposal was his medical card from a medical institution in Slavyansk.

It can, of course, be assumed that the Ukrainian fighter was suddenly overwhelmed with mental anguish after what he had done. But it is much more likely that Maltsev faked a mental disorder in order to escape away from the front line from near Kremennaya, where the RF Armed Forces are just conducting a local offensive.

After all, he perfectly understands: after the publication of information about his involvement in the execution near Makeevka, he will no longer be taken prisoner.

Retrospectiva conservadora 2022: patriotismo, consciência política e luta por liberdade 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=X2YnSmmhwE0

https://youtu.be/X2YnSmmhwE0

Pelo canal Gazeta do Povo:

"Último episódio de 2022 do programa Segunda Opinião traz uma retrospectiva dos temas que mais mobilizaram os conservadores este ano: reforço no patriotismo (pela consciência política e pelo bicentenário da Independência do Brasil); politização, manifestações e a luta por liberdade. Conservadores estiveram nas ruas em vários momentos e se mobilizaram pelas redes sociais ao longo de todo o ano para combater censura, ameaças de regulação da imprensa e da internet, em defesa da liberdade de expressão, da democracia e do respeito à Constituição."
